Classic Load Balancer:

To apply load balancer both the ec2 instances are in different availability zones 
Create two ec2 instances and install nginx on both the instances and start the nginx server 
###################
amazon-linux-extras install nginx1 (amazon linux2)
Check the nginx server status and start the nginx server
#############
service nginx status
service nginx start
Check the nginx port is active 
################
netstat -plunt | grep :80
To identify the difference of output generated by nginx server index.html after applyling load balancer update index.html content either in server1 or server2
nginx index.html path.localtion
/usr/share/nginx/html
############
vi index.html

 <h1>Welcome to <strong>nginx</strong> on Amazon Linux! updating content for laod balancer</h1>
 
 After making changes in index.hmtl restart nginx server
 ##############
  service nginx restart
 

Before creating load balancer check the nginx home page is loading or not in browser 
Allow port number 80 in security groups
http://3.237.69.140/ 
http://54.237.110.240/
